CI - Continuous Integration:
    . A process where team members integrate their work Continuously in a shared repository.
    . Best achieved using some SCM tools like GIT-Bitbucket.
    . Can be daily or as needed integration or checkin in the repo is validated by automated build,
      automated unit or integration tests.
    

CD - Continuous Delivery:
    . After the CI process, Deployment on a production like environment and running automation tests to
      ensure the build is ready for release.
    . Ensures the build is always in a Deployable state.
    . It includes from dev, test and staging environment.
    . Staging is production like environment, also called as pre-prod environment.


CD - Continuous Deployment:
    . Automated Deployment to prod
    . Every change that passes through automation tests is deployed to production.

